{"word":"G5429 - φρόνιμος - phrónimos - fron'-ee-mos - Wise","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">φρόνιμος</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">phrónimos</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">fron'-ee-mos</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">Wise</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>Adjective / பெயரடை</span>"},{"paragraph":"புத்தியுள்ள, வினாவுள்ள, விவேகமுள்ள, புத்திமான்களான - பெயரடை"},{"paragraph":"1. intelligent, wise"},{"paragraph":"2. prudent, mindful of one's interests"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>From <a href=\"#/G5424 - φρήν - phrḗn - frane/5424\">G5424</a>; <i>thoughtful</i>, that is, <i>sagacious</i> or <i>discreet</i> (implying a <i>cautious</i> character; while <a href=\"#/G4680 - σοφός - sophós - sof-os'/4680\">G4680</a> denotes <i>practical</i> skill or acumen; and <a href=\"#/G4908 - συνετός - synetós - soon-et'-os/4908\">G4908</a> indicates rather <i>intelligence</i> or mental acquirement); in a bad sense <i>conceited</i> (also in the comparative): - wise (-r).</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>தொடர்புடைய எண்கள் / Cognate: </strong><a href=\"#/G5424/5424\">G5424</a>, <a href=\"#/G5426/5426\">G5426</a>, <a href=\"#/G5427/5427\">G5427</a>, <a href=\"#/G5428/5428\">G5428</a>, <a href=\"#/G5429/5429\">G5429</a>, <a href=\"#/G5430/5430\">G5430</a>, <a href=\"#/G877/877\">G877</a>, <a href=\"#/G878/878\">G878</a>"}]}